Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of device-to-device (D2D) communications in uplink (UL) cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry theory to derive the coverage probability and area spectral efficiency (ASE), which are concepts related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a framework for analyzing the performance of D2D communications, which can be seen as a system in a cellular network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not explicitly mention multimedia, but D2D communications can be used for multimedia applications such as video streaming and file sharing. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not focus on cryptography and security, but these topics may be relevant in the context of D2D communications in cellular networks.
